    <string name="bluetooth_lowend_warning_content">To support more devices with the Bluetooth Proxy Gateway and improve compatibility with Bermuda integration, we have optimized for low-end BLE 4.0 chips and below BLE 5.0.\n\nSpecial thanks to @agittins for the excellent Bermuda integration, and the handsome gentleman @daydy16 for raising this issue.\n\nImportant Notes:\n- Scan frequency is reduced to ensure stable WiFi performance\n- Bermuda may show skull or exclamation icons occasionally - this is normal, internal optimization is active\n- Bluetooth media playback is not supported as we need to continuously reset the Bluetooth adapter to send data to Home Assistant\n- Root access is required for this feature\n- Built-in Bluetooth presence detection is disabled for BLE 4.0 chips\n\nFor full features including presence detection and advanced capabilities, please use an Android device with Bluetooth 5.0 or above.</string>
    
